1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:15,233
<i>Fellow citizens, let's vote,
Amo, Mayor of Calabari!</i>

2
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

3
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:19,567
<i>Sonny really doesn't want
to tell me about his job.</i>

4
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,800
<i>But believe me,
Amo is a bad person.</i>

5
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:24,467
<i>This is what was taken
from our back exit.</i>

6
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,933
<i> Isn't that scary?</i>

7
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:29,367
<i>Well, the gunman escaped,
and we were recognized.</i>

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:30,833
<i> Maybe he'll come back for us.</i>

9
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:35,300
<i>Selena told me she saw Amo
and Sonny talking the day</i>

10
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:36,667
<i> before the kidnapping.</i>

11
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,400
<i>They don't accept hunches
in court.</i>

12
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:43,033
<i>Only evidence is true,
not our opinions.</i>

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,867
Sir, here are the things seized
from the suspects.

14
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:32,733
Mar!

15
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:37,267
I already talked to Vince, Lee,
and Bal.

16
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,200
Now, they're on their way here.

17
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,200
Why?

18
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,700
What can those ugly people
do to help us?

19
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:50,567
Well, we can't be in the Witness
Protection Program, right?

20
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:53,100
So let's get them as our
bodyguards.

21
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:55,000
Well, I already talked to them.

22
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:58,433
They agreed to watch over us
on 24/7.

23
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:04,200
But the thing is, it's P450 per
night, and then there's dinner.

24
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:06,600
At least we're safe, right?

25
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:08,200
Well, you have a point,

26
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,267
so that the killer can't easily
approach us.

27
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,167
That's right.

28
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:16,300
Hey, what killer
are you talking about?

29
00:02:16,467 --> 00:02:19,367
Kapitana, do you remember
Mysterious Oppa?

30
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,200
Yes.

31
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:23,433
He's the one who shot
the riders on the highway,

32
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:27,033
and he's also the sniper
at the fiesta.

33
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:29,433
He might get back at Abdul
and me.

34
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:31,167
It's better that we have
a bodyguard.

35
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,333
That's scary.

36
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:36,233
Oh my, be careful, huh?

37
00:02:36,367 --> 00:02:37,000
Yes.

38
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:38,167
Thank you, Kapitana.

39
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,800
Kapitana, thank you.

40
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:42,167
Okay, I'll go to our barangay
hall first.

41
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,733
- Okay, be careful.
- You should follow.

42
00:02:43,867 --> 00:02:44,767
Be careful.

43
00:02:45,467 --> 00:02:47,133
Never mind at least, we're safe,
right?

44
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:54,667
This is not enough.

45
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:59,200
You know it's not easy to find
the address of the safehouses,

46
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,000
right?

47
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:07,000
This would have been thicker
if you had killed Selena.

48
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,033
I've lost one more person.

49
00:03:09,167 --> 00:03:10,133
Bullet is gone.

50
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:12,467
My Korean still got hit in
the shoulder.

51
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,467
What else do you expect?

52
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,733
Okay, okay, okay.

53
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:20,167
But can you please not contact
me for now?

54
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,200
Why?

55
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:24,300
I'm just being careful.

56
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,233
Chief saw me talking to your
Korean sniper

57
00:03:29,367 --> 00:03:30,733
when he went to the police
station.

58
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,767
And our biggest problem now

59
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:37,067
is that a civilian recognized
him.

60
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:40,800
A civilian recognized him?

61
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,100
Who?

62
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:45,433
Where does he live?

63
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:46,633
Why?

64
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:47,800
What are you going to do?

65
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,167
No one else can know Woo.

66
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:55,767
They need to be killed.

67
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:02,300
<i> Selena confided in me earlier</i>

68
00:04:02,433 --> 00:04:04,400
<i>and she identified
that the assassin who died</i>

69
00:04:04,533 --> 00:04:07,800
<i> as Sonny's coworker.</i>

70
00:04:07,933 --> 00:04:10,300
<i>And the one they're pointing to
as their boss and mastermind</i>

71
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:12,333
<i>in the case we're investigating</i>

72
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:16,367
<i>is none other than Victor
Santiago.</i>

73
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,067
<i>So why does his boss have
so much money?</i>

74
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:22,300
<i> Where is that coming from?</i>

75
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:24,967
<i>Where else but from
the public funds?</i>

76
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:42,967
What do you need?

77
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,667
Tonyo, my Son...

78
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:47,300
I heard from your Chief
that there was a shootout

79
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:48,533
at the safehouse.

80
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:49,367
Are you okay?

81
00:04:53,267 --> 00:04:54,367
I'm still alive.

82
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:56,600
Do you need anything?

83
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:58,067
I'm busy right now.

84
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:03,500
Let's talk next time,
but we have a lot to talk about.

85
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:11,300
Excuse me, Sir.

86
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:13,033
I've endorsed Selena.

87
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:15,100
Her escorts are with her.

88
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:19,100
I've also marked the suspects'
belongings, including the guns.

89
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:20,633
Good.

90
00:05:21,933 --> 00:05:23,633
We can go back to Calabari.

91
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:28,367
Sir, who are you talking to?

92
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:34,633
It's none of your business,
Enriquez.

93
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:36,800
And please,

94
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,433
can you stop listening to other
people's conversations?

95
00:05:48,367 --> 00:05:49,267
Hey, Daga.

96
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:52,233
Be grateful the Mayor didn't
file a complaint against you.

97
00:05:52,367 --> 00:05:54,733
Next time, I don't want
to see you throwing eggs.

98
00:05:54,867 --> 00:05:55,800
Hey, Daga!

99
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,800
Pay for my goods.

100
00:05:57,933 --> 00:05:59,400
Did you think you could
get away with it?

101
00:05:59,533 --> 00:06:01,800
What about my income for today?

102
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:03,633
I'm just making a living here.

103
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:05,367
What?

104
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,233
Pay up!

105
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,533
Hello!

106
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,000
How much is it?

107
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,067
One thousand five hundred,
total.

108
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:12,600
One thousand five hundred.

109
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:13,533
What?

110
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,000
It's only one thousand
five hundred.

111
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,400
You nag as if you thought...

112
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:19,800
Here.

113
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,767
That's P3,000.

114
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:22,733
Okay!

115
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:27,033
You know, even if you bump
into me every day, it's okay.

116
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:28,600
Thank you!

117
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,767
Before, you were running
away for twenty pesos.

118
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,533
Now, P3,000?

119
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:35,533
There's nothing we can do.
That's just how life is.

120
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:38,200
Sometimes, you're down.
Sometimes, you're lucky.

121
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:39,867
Okay, okay, okay, go away.

122
00:06:40,867 --> 00:06:41,900
That's okay, huh?

123
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:42,933
- Sir.
- Next time, huh.

124
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:45,067
Keep up the good work.

125
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:46,700
Next time again.

126
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,133
That's 3k?

127
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:52,867
Hi, Ms. Beautiful.

128
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,367
Can I ask a question?

129
00:06:54,667 --> 00:06:55,533
What's that?

130
00:06:56,033 --> 00:06:57,933
Do you know where Daga works?

131
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:00,000
I'd like to interview him.

132
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,133
Oh my, he's unemployed.

133
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:03,433
He's always hanging out
at the market with his gang.

134
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:07,000
He's jobless, but he's generous?

135
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,600
Maybe he has a lover who
supports him?

136
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:13,267
But you know, let me tell you,
after the hostage taking here.

137
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,500
It seems like there
was a lifestyle change

138
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,267
among his gangmates

139
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:21,133
Because they paid off all their
debts to me, plus tips.

140
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:23,933
I have a feeling that they were
affected by what Amo said.

141
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,633
Okay, good luck with the
interview.

142
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:28,733
Thank you.

143
00:07:28,867 --> 00:07:31,067
If you still need someone,
I'm available.

144
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:32,500
Thank you, Miss.

145
00:07:32,633 --> 00:07:33,233
Thank you!

146
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:42,600
Come in!

147
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:47,467
Doc.

148
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:48,800
Hi, Doc.

149
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:51,200
Lieutenant Conde,
Sergeant Enriquez.

150
00:07:52,767 --> 00:07:54,533
What's your gift
to me this time?

151
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:57,500
This is Bullet.

152
00:07:58,033 --> 00:08:00,867
Male, mid-30s, five-nine,
five-ten.

153
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,433
Maybe 185 pounds.

154
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:06,533
Time of death, 6 to 7 hours ago.

155
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,500
What's the case?

156
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:17,633
Murder, frustrated murder,
homicide, and carnapping.

157
00:08:18,233 --> 00:08:21,100
is this related to your first
suspect, Sonny?

158
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,367
His colleague, Doc.

159
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,667
Most likely,

160
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:27,233
he was with him in the
San Isidro bank robbery

161
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:30,200
and the kidnapping
of Faye Guerrero.

162
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,933
So you still don't have a lead
on the mastermind

163
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:34,500
or person of interest?

164
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:35,900
- There is.
- Nothing conclusive yet.

165
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,333
Conde, the Major is calling us.

166
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:48,233
Lieutenant Garcia.

167
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:53,133
Nice to see you! I missed you!

168
00:08:57,367 --> 00:09:01,033
Anyway, I'll bring you a partial
report tomorrow.

169
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:02,600
Okay, Doc.

170
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:03,700
- Okay.
- Thank you, Doc.

171
00:09:04,733 --> 00:09:05,200
Bok.

172
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,033
Sir.

173
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:12,233
Lieutenant Garcia, do you need
anything else?

174
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,067
You...

175
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,967
Sorry, it's overwhelming.

176
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,533
How about you,
do you need anything, Doc?

177
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:20,967
Because...

178
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:23,033
you miss...

179
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:24,133
you miss, right?

180
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,433
Okay.

181
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:35,900
Sir, Bullet's body has been
turned over to Doc Cecilia,

182
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:39,667
and the forensic autopsy
is available tomorrow.

183
00:09:39,967 --> 00:09:42,167
All the suspects' guns are
also at SOCO,

184
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,900
and we've already gone through
Bullet's wallet and cell phone.

185
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:46,100
Clean.

186
00:09:46,233 --> 00:09:47,100
Clean?

187
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:48,200
That means, Sir,

188
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:52,567
there is no evidence linking
bullet to anyone.

189
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:56,433
Sir, based on the evidence,
we don't have a name yet,

190
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:59,600
but Miss Selena has spoken,

191
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:03,733
and the one she's pointing
to is Victor Santiago.

192
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:06,833
Is it Boss Amo again?

193
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,367
But he's still not a person
of interest

194
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,867
just because Selena
mentioned him.

195
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:15,000
A person of interest is someone
whom law enforcement

196
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:17,567
believes may have information
about the crime,

197
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,400
and I believe Amo knows
something.

198
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:21,633
But, Enriquez...

199
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:22,933
Let's do another step...

200
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:28,433
because I want to make sure
before this gets out.

201
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:30,233
Search Bullet's house.

202
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:32,867
And if you find anyone connected
to Amo,

203
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,800
that's when we'll invite him
there.

204
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,500
Sir, can I take the day off?

205
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:38,000
I'll just rest for now.

206
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,267
Okay, Conde.

207
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:47,800
Doc, excuse me.

208
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,667
Thank you.

209
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:51,367
This is what you're asking for.

210
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:52,400
Thank you.

211
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,567
This is interesting.

212
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,700
I've heard of retained bullet
fragments in the head.

213
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,400
This is a full bullet.

214
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:09,033
Doc, how long do you think
that was in his brain?

215
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,967
When we extract it, we'll know.

216
00:11:12,267 --> 00:11:14,367
And then we can run a ballistic
fingerprinting

217
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:18,467
to find out what gun
this bullet came from.

218
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:19,833
Thank you.

219
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:20,633
Thank you, Doc.

220
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:27,900
Enriquez, can I ask a question?

221
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:30,567
Sir, what's that?

222
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:33,767
No, not anymore.

223
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,567
No, Sir, Sir, it's okay.

224
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,200
What...

225
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,067
What's that?

226
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:39,667
But...

227
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:44,500
But promise me you won't get mad
or jealous, okay?

228
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,900
Yes, Sir, promise.

229
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,367
Okay.

230
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,133
I want to start clean.

231
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:57,700
Let's just be friends.

232
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:00,333
Wait.

233
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:00,700
Just process it first.

234
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:01,867
Okay.

235
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,333
Question.

236
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:10,100
Does Doc Cecilia have a
boyfriend?

237
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:13,833
It seems...

238
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:14,900
it seems none, Sir.

239
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:16,200
She's busy.

240
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,400
I knew it.

241
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,100
I'm the only one she's waiting
for to make the first move.

242
00:12:24,233 --> 00:12:25,733
You have a really big chance,
Sir.

243
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:26,467
Isn't that right, Bautista?

244
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,100
Yes.

245
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,100
Really?

246
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:30,133
Yes, because, Sir,
think about it.

247
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:33,900
Your rivals with the Doctor
are corpses of criminals.

248
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,133
But did you know

249
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:39,000
that Bullet even got a date
with Doctora before him?

250
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:40,333
Yes, that's right?

251
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,333
Hey, hey, hey!

252
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:45,133
You two, you act like I'm not
your senior.

253
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,933
Hey, let me just make it clear
to you.

254
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:52,433
I know Doc is head over heels
with me.

255
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:53,933
She's so into me.

256
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,000
Let's bet on that, P1,000.

257
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:57,733
What?

258
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:58,633
Okay, I go for nothing And you?

259
00:12:58,767 --> 00:13:00,733
Of course, I go for nothing too.

260
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:03,600
You'll lose your eyelashes now.

261
00:13:03,733 --> 00:13:06,533
Give it to me. All your money
will be gone, for sure.

262
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:07,867
Okay, that's enough.

263
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:12,800
Sir, Enriquez, you just promised
me you wouldn't be angry.

264
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:13,633
Sir.

265
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:15,967
Where are you going?

266
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:17,500
I'm going home.

267
00:13:19,267 --> 00:13:20,533
Sir, won't you come with us?

268
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:21,933
We'll drop you off.

269
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:24,033
No need.

270
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:28,800
He's so grumpy.

271
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:35,800
Miss, do you know Daga?

272
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:37,467
Do you know where his house is?

273
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,233
Oh, my Ms.Beautiful,
I don't know.

274
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:41,467
Thank you.

275
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:49,867
Mister, just a moment?

276
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:51,600
Hello, Daga?

277
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:54,467
Yes, I'm here.

278
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:57,267
Are you sure I'm just going
to put this here?

279
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,167
Don't blame me if this goes
missing.

280
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,100
All right, all right.

281
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:10,300
Mister, let's go.

282
00:14:22,667 --> 00:14:25,267
What's Amo's secretary doing
here?

283
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:35,467
Daga?

284
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,267
So Amo paid you to throw eggs
at the Mayor.

285
00:14:55,233 --> 00:14:57,000
What are you talking about,
Ms. Tisay?

286
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:03,233
You know, if that's your pickup
line to get my number I'm sorry.

287
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,367
You're not my type.

288
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,167
I'll triple it.

289
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:13,233
Whatever Amo gave you,
I'll triple it.

290
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:22,033
In exchange for what?

291
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:25,200
Tell me everything Amo
made you do.

292
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:32,533
Triple?

293
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,500
What's with Bullet?

294
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:41,733
He turned his laundry
into a mattress.

295
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,867
- Hey, Lieutenant Robles.
- Bok.

296
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:50,333
What else can I help you with?

297
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,533
Here, here.

298
00:15:54,267 --> 00:15:55,067
Later, open this.

299
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,467
You can take care of the briefs.

300
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:04,000
It's a good thing
Lieutenant Robles is here

301
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:05,033
for the investigation.

302
00:16:05,167 --> 00:16:08,933
Meanwhile, my companion
is missing in action.

303
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,767
Why don't you go straight
to the point?

304
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,433
Mention Conde's name.

305
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:15,967
He's the only one not here.

306
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:17,800
You know,

307
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:23,400
I thought you and Conde would be
close after you guarded Selena,

308
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:25,633
but it seems like the opposite
happened.

309
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:27,767
I don't know with him.

310
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:32,400
Why can't he entertain the idea

311
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:36,300
that Amo could have done all
this?

312
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,467
Why is that? Is that his idol?

313
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:41,733
Well, as for me, he is my idol.

314
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:43,700
But him? He's not his idol.

315
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:46,600
He doesn't know anything
about 90s shows.

316
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:50,467
He doesn't watch the old movies.

317
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,167
Why doesn't he watch them?

318
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:55,233
He should because he looks
exactly like Amo

319
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:56,733
when he was younger.

320
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,767
They could be father and son.

321
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,633
Hey, what are you doing?

322
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,300
We're preparing for
the upcoming trials.

323
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:19,833
We'll take care of you.

324
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,133
- You know, in the face...
- We'll save you from evil!

325
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:24,533
Just looking at your face,
the sniper Oppa will be scared.

326
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:25,500
Especially him.

327
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:28,833
It's scary.

328
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,767
Mar, Abdul!

329
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:31,700
Snack time!

330
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:32,733
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

331
00:17:32,867 --> 00:17:34,500
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

332
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:36,633
What's that? Dude, smell it.
There might be a bomb in there.

333
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:37,500
Hey! Smell it, smell it.

334
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:38,400
Oops! It smells like fish.

335
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:40,200
You're doing something
suspicious.

336
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:42,000
What you're doing is illegal.

337
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,567
I'm just delivering lumpia
to Kapitana.

338
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,367
What are you doing?

339
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,000
What's that?

340
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:48,133
Wait, wait, don't be stubborn.

341
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,567
- What's that? Oh, this.
- It's lumpia.

342
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,067
-You guys should just go for it.
-Snack.

343
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:53,667
- No, they'll pay.
- We don't have this, Ms Abi.

344
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:54,833
You should treat us...

345
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:55,767
Take two for us.

346
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,800
We're working.
How can we be strong?

347
00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:58,433
We can't...

348
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:00,333
Just fix your work.

349
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:03,000
Boss, I'm already at the house
of two targets.

350
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:04,733
But there are a lot of pests.

351
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:07,867
Just don't move while the
policewoman is there, clear?

352
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,033
Okay...

353
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:11,800
It seems like these have been in
the sun for a long time.

354
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:12,733
What's this?

355
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:17,767
Sugar-filled dumplings?

356
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:18,500
You're annoying.

357
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:19,700
Give it to me..

358
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,233
Balut...

359
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,267
are you going to buy?

360
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:28,367
Balut!

361
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,967
What are you busy with here?

362
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:30,967
Hi, Ma'am!

363
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,767
Snack time!

364
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:36,000
Hey, balut, balut, come here.
We're going to buy.

365
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:36,967
Hey!

366
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:40,967
Payment? Give it to me.

367
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,500
Where is Kapitana?

368
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:43,667
At the barangay hall,

369
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:44,867
she's been there for a while
now!

370
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,533
Okay, I'll just go there.

371
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:47,733
I'll join you.

372
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:53,300
Let's go there.

373
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:54,467
Dude, take care of it.

374
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,333
- Hey, what is it?
- Thank you, Ms. Abi.

375
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:57,633
We'll be back.

376
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,933
We saw his face.

377
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:07,267
That's why Mar and I were just
being careful.

378
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,467
How would we know

379
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,300
that Mysterious Oppa was the
hired killer?

380
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:12,467
Yes, that's right,

381
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,800
and is it really enough
that someone who looks like

382
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:16,333
an addict is watching outside?

383
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,733
My God, Abdul, let's undergo
a cosmetic surgery

384
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,467
so that we'd look like a woman.

385
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:23,167
Hey, you're not just after
a nose job.

386
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:24,900
You want to change your entire
character, right?

387
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:25,667
Yes, correct.

388
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,533
Don't do that.

389
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:27,567
You're so OA.

390
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,267
You're not his target.

391
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:31,300
Maybe he won't recognize you.

392
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:34,000
The Mayor should be replaced.

393
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:37,867
Well, since he took office,
there's been a lot of crime.

394
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:38,833
Correct.

395
00:19:39,167 --> 00:19:41,100
You know, Amo won the debate.

396
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:45,200
Imagine, his answers are
better than the Mayor's.

397
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:46,300
It's true.

398
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,533
I have a favorite of his,
women's rights.

399
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:50,300
That's his platform,
I love it, that's my favorite.

400
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:51,567
I love it.

401
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,267
Women's rights,
women's rights.

402
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:56,067
Well, during his peak of
popularity, he hurt women.

403
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,633
No, that's not true.

404
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:01,000
You're a fan, Kapitana.

405
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:03,267
Did you know that his
non-showbiz ex

406
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:04,667
sent him to prison?

407
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:07,633
Are you saying that Amo
has a criminal record?

408
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,800
- Noble, did you get it?
- Oh, Ma'am.

409
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:18,000
Yes, this is it.

410
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,233
Thank you.
Here, have coffee first.

411
00:20:26,367 --> 00:20:29,400
Ma'am, do you think people will
believe

412
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:32,333
that Amo has connections
to criminal activities?

413
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:33,567
His ratings are still high,

414
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:35,300
and people still love him very
much.

415
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,633
Maybe later,

416
00:20:37,767 --> 00:20:39,500
they will say this
is a demolition job for Amo.

417
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:45,933
Sir Tonyo said, only evidence
is true and not our opinion.

418
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:57,167
There are still flowers here.

419
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:08,300
The woman, later identified as
Miss Marissa Conde,

420
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:10,167
5 months pregnant,

421
00:21:11,067 --> 00:21:12,833
appeared distressed but
unharmed.

422
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:20,367
Marissa Conde,
5 months pregnant.

423
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:21,733
Conde?

424
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,433
Same last name as Sir Tonyo's?

425
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:51,467
Tonyo.

426
00:21:55,267 --> 00:21:56,167
Can we talk?

427
00:22:02,867 --> 00:22:03,600
Thank you.

428
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:11,700
Thank you for granting
my request here.

429
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,767
Stop giving flowers
to my Mother.

430
00:22:16,133 --> 00:22:17,333
Didn't you leave her?

431
00:22:18,667 --> 00:22:22,667
And to this day,
that is my biggest regret

432
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:26,367
choosing my career
over Melinda and you.

433
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,733
Don't involve me in that.

434
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:32,733
You were also not there
when I was born, right?

435
00:22:34,133 --> 00:22:35,667
That's why we don't
have a relationship.

436
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:39,600
With my mother,
that's where you're accountable.

437
00:22:42,867 --> 00:22:43,833
I want to make up for it.

438
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:45,467
To who?

439
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:48,133
My mother is gone.

440
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:50,000
You're still here.

441
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,200
I don't need your help.

442
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:58,633
I know.

443
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:03,900
But remember, the door of my
house is always open for you.

444
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:29,167
Hello, Chief?

445
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:30,133
Good morning!

446
00:23:30,267 --> 00:23:32,200
Conde, I've been calling you
for a while.

447
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:34,667
I'm sorry, Chief.
My phone is on silent.

448
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,500
Check the link I sent you right
away and watch it right away.

449
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:38,600
Okay, copy, Sir.

450
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,933
Daga, how much did you guys get
paid?

451
00:23:48,067 --> 00:23:50,033
Twenty thousand each.

452
00:23:50,167 --> 00:23:52,633
We're a group of ten,
so 200,000 in total.

453
00:23:52,933 --> 00:23:54,433
Just to throw eggs?

454
00:23:56,467 --> 00:23:57,900
Amo has a lot of money, right?

455
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,600
And that's not all we did
for him.

456
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:05,533
He paid us more than a million
to cause trouble in the league

457
00:24:06,133 --> 00:24:10,300
and take hostages so that he
would look like a hero

458
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:11,933
in the eyes of the voters.

459
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:13,900
Apparently,

460
00:24:14,333 --> 00:24:18,700
all of that was scripted just to
boost his name for the election!

461
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:20,700
But why are you confessing now?

462
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,800
Well, we feel guilty.

463
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:24,033
But it's up to you.

464
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:27,667
Think carefully about whether
you'll vote for Amo

465
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:30,033
if all he's doing is lying.

466
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,267
So he would win!

467
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,667
Damn!

468
00:24:33,133 --> 00:24:35,100
You're a bunch of jerks!

469
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:38,600
Miss, here's my payment.

470
00:24:49,233 --> 00:24:50,667
I've been waiting for you
for a while, Sir.

471
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:52,433
Why, Enriquez?

472
00:24:53,067 --> 00:24:54,767
I wanted to ask you something.

473
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:57,767
Let's talk later.

474
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,700
I have something important
to take care of.

475
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:03,533
Amo is your father, right, Sir?

476
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:23,800
Because Selena's claim
that Victor Santiago

477
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:25,300
is the mastermind of Sonny
and Bullet is meaningless

478
00:25:25,433 --> 00:25:27,933
if we can't back it up
with solid evidence.

479
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:29,167
How about the sniper?

480
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:30,267
Have you heard from him?

481
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:33,167
Nothing yet, Sir,
but I'm sure he's not far off.

482
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,433
Maybe you want him to feel
guilty,

483
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,933
so you have a reason
to not like him

484
00:25:38,067 --> 00:25:40,533
because you're starting
to like him.

485
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:42,233
Grandmother, I don't like him.

486
00:25:42,367 --> 00:25:44,833
Didn't we recognize Oppa Sniper?

487
00:25:44,967 --> 00:25:47,933
Abdul and I are nervous.
Maybe he'll kill us later.

488
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:48,900
Yes, Bobby.

489
00:25:49,033 --> 00:25:51,900
Then there's someone who's not
from here.

490
00:25:52,033 --> 00:25:53,667
Well, maybe that's a suspect.
